Description: Fragment of a wooden coffin; decorated in paint on plaster on both sides: two lines of blue hieroglyphic text on one side and an object frieze (with jars and a head rest) on the other.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Bibliographic references: Zitman 2010 / The necropolis of Assiut: a case study of local Egyptian funerary culture from the Old Kingdom to the end of the Middle Kingdom (II, 113, 215)
